{"id": "EUVD-2025-5157", "enisaUuid": "44aabc9c-f2a7-3d7c-b937-0a16b15d0fb4", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nipv6: mcast: extend RCU protection in igmp6_send()\n\nigmp6_send() can be called without RTNL or RCU being held.\n\nExtend RCU protection so that we can safely fetch the net pointer\nand avoid a potential UAF.\n\nNote that we no longer can use sock_alloc_send_skb() because\nipv6.igmp_sk uses GFP_KERNEL allocations which can sleep.\n\nInstead use alloc_skb() and charge the net->ipv6.igmp_sk\nsocket under RCU protection.", "datePublished": "2025-02-27T02:18:12", "dateUpdated": "2025-03-24T15:39:55", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-21759", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/087c1faa594fa07a66933d750c0b2610aa1a2946", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0bf8e2f3768629d437a32cb824149e6e98254381", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/81b25a07ebf53f9ef4ca8f3d96a8ddb94561dd5a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8e92d6a413feaf968a33f0b439ecf27404407458"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-21759", "GHSA-pvj3-f5v8-hgxh"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1e37316a-4933-389f-8646-8840025b105f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b8ad0cbc58f703972e9e37c4e2a8081dd7e6a551 <81b25a07ebf53f9ef4ca8f3d96a8ddb94561dd5a"}, {"id": "2d467b15-fa5d-39a9-9087-7d3e1d30ca0b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.16"}, {"id": "4aca728d-3dd5-3a28-a2e0-98f22e866c3d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.13.4"}, {"id": "6b1bcab9-6565-3055-8111-e182a92422a0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b8ad0cbc58f703972e9e37c4e2a8081dd7e6a551 <087c1faa594fa07a66933d750c0b2610aa1a2946"}, {"id": "76d5db52-9219-3cc4-a614-dd2e4f300457", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "b8ad0cbc58f703972e9e37c4e2a8081dd7e6a551 <8e92d6a